<div class="mt-16">
    <Heading Id="api-reference" Level="2" Class="scroll-mt-20">API Reference</Heading>
    <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Class="mt-2">
        Every typed chart (<code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">BarChart</code>,
        <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">LineChart</code>, …) wraps the underlying
        <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">Chart</code> primitive documented below and forwards
        its loading/theming/event parameters through. See each chart type's own page (under
        <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/components/charts/*</code>) for its data-shaping
        parameters (<code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">Categories</code>,
        <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">Series</code>, etc.).
    </Lumeo.Text>

    <Heading Id="chart" Level="3" Class="mt-8 scroll-mt-20">Chart</Heading>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
        <Table>
            <TableHeader>
                <TableRow>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Prop</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Type</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[120px]">Default</TableHead>
                    <TableHead>Description</TableHead>
                </TableRow>
            </TableHeader>
            <TableBody>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Option</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">EChartOption?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Strongly-typed ECharts option. Mutually usable alongside OptionJson; when both are set, OptionJson wins.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">OptionJson</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Raw ECharts option as a JSON string. Takes precedence over Option when set.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ChildContent</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">RenderFragment?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Declarative annotation children — ChartThreshold and ChartReferenceZone. Other content renders nothing visible.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Theme</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>ECharts theme name to initialize the chart with.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">EChartsSource</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Per-chart override for the core ECharts script URL, redirecting this chart off the jsDelivr CDN onto a self-hosted copy.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">AriaLabel</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Accessible text alternative for the chart (WCAG 1.1.1). When set, the canvas host is exposed as role="img" with this aria-label so screen readers announce a summary instead of an empty graphic. Strongly recommended.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">AccessibilityLayer</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">bool</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">true</TableCell><TableCell>When true (shadcn accessibilityLayer parity), renders a visually-hidden data table built from the series data and makes the canvas host keyboard-focusable with a summarising aria-label. Set to false to opt out.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">MaxAccessibilityRows</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">int</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">50</TableCell><TableCell>Upper bound on the number of data rows the hidden screen-reader table materializes. Above the cap the table keeps the first N rows plus an "… and N more data points" row. Set to 0 (or negative) to disable the cap and render every row.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Width</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">"100%"</TableCell><TableCell>CSS width of the chart host.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Height</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">"350px"</TableCell><TableCell>CSS height of the chart host. Ignored when AspectRatio is set.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">AspectRatio</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>CSS aspect-ratio for the chart host (e.g. "16 / 9"). When set, the host's height is derived from Width and this ratio instead of Height.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Group</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Connects this chart to other charts sharing the same group name so cursor/zoom actions sync across them (ECharts connect group).</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ShowLoading</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">bool</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">false</TableCell><TableCell>Shows ECharts' own native loading indicator overlay (independent of the Lumeo skeleton/phantom loading state below).</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">OnClick</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">EventCallback&lt;ChartEventArgs&gt;</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">—</TableCell><TableCell>Fires on a click on any chart element (series point, legend, etc.).</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">OnMouseOver</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">EventCallback&lt;ChartEventArgs&gt;</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">—</TableCell><TableCell>Fires when the pointer moves over a chart element.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">OnDoubleClick</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">EventCallback&lt;ChartEventArgs&gt;</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">—</TableCell><TableCell>Fires on a double-click on a chart element.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">OnBrushSelected</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">EventCallback&lt;ChartEventArgs&gt;</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">—</TableCell><TableCell>Fires when a brush selection is made (requires a brush component in the option).</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">OnDataZoom</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">EventCallback&lt;ChartEventArgs&gt;</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">—</TableCell><TableCell>Fires when the user zooms/pans a dataZoom component.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">OnInitError</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">EventCallback&lt;string&gt;</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">—</TableCell><TableCell>Fires with the error message when ECharts initialization fails (e.g. the CDN script failed to load). The chart renders an inline error state instead of the canvas.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">IsLoading</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">bool</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">false</TableCell><TableCell>When true, forces the Lumeo loading state (skeleton or phantom data) on top of the chart — set while the consumer refetches data.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ShowLoadingSkeleton</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">bool</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">true</TableCell><TableCell>When true, renders the loading state while the chart has not yet rendered for the first time, and whenever IsLoading is true. Set to false to opt out entirely.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">SkeletonKind</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ChartSkeletonKind</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Generic</TableCell><TableCell>Shape family for the loading skeleton/phantom data. Each typed chart wrapper presets a sensible default (bars for Bar, pie ring for Pie, etc.).</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">SkeletonStyle</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ChartSkeletonStyle</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Phantom</TableCell><TableCell>Phantom (default) renders the real chart with synthesized placeholder data in a muted palette that animates to real data. Silhouette falls back to a legacy SVG overlay skeleton.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">PhantomCycleMs</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">int</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">1400</TableCell><TableCell>Phantom-mode refresh interval in milliseconds — each tick regenerates the placeholder dataset with a new random seed. Clamped to ≥200ms.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">PhantomShapeOverride</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">PhantomShape?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Explicit override for the phantom layout (category count, series count, stacking, area fill). When null (default), the shape is inferred from the real Option so the phantom mirrors the actual chart structure.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ShowLoadingLabel</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">bool</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">true</TableCell><TableCell>When true, overlays a small top-right pill (spinner + LoadingText) on top of the active skeleton — a clear, always-on visual cue that the chart is loading. Set to false for bare visuals.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">LoadingText</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Label rendered next to the spinner inside the loading pill. Set to null or empty to hide the text and show only the spinner. Defaults to the active locale's "Loading…" string.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Class</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Additional CSS classes.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">AdditionalAttributes</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Dictionary&lt;string, object&gt;?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Additional HTML attributes.</TableCell></TableRow>
            </TableBody>
        </Table>
    </div>

    <Heading Id="chartthreshold" Level="3" Class="mt-8 scroll-mt-20">ChartThreshold</Heading>
    <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Class="mt-2">
        Declarative threshold line — a horizontal (default) or vertical marker at a given value. Place inside any
        typed chart's <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">ChildContent</code>; it renders nothing
        visible itself and instead registers a <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">markLine</code>
        entry on the underlying option.
    </Lumeo.Text>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
        <Table>
            <TableHeader>
                <TableRow>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Prop</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Type</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[120px]">Default</TableHead>
                    <TableHead>Description</TableHead>
                </TableRow>
            </TableHeader>
            <TableBody>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Value</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">object</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">0</TableCell><TableCell>Value on the perpendicular axis (yAxis for horizontal, xAxis for vertical). Required.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Axis</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ChartThresholdAxis</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Horizontal</TableCell><TableCell>Which axis the line is perpendicular to — Horizontal draws a yAxis line spanning the chart width (the common target/SLA line); Vertical draws an xAxis line.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Label</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Label rendered along the line. Null or empty hides it.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Color</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Hex / CSS colour for the line. When null, ECharts inherits the series colour.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">LineStyle</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">"dashed"</TableCell><TableCell>Line style passed to ECharts — "solid", "dashed", or "dotted". Defaults to dashed for visual distinction from data lines.</TableCell></TableRow>
            </TableBody>
        </Table>
    </div>

    <Heading Id="chartreferencezone" Level="3" Class="mt-8 scroll-mt-20">ChartReferenceZone</Heading>
    <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Class="mt-2">
        Declarative reference band — a shaded rectangle between two values on one axis, spanning the full extent of
        the other. Wraps ECharts' native <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">markArea</code>.
    </Lumeo.Text>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
        <Table>
            <TableHeader>
                <TableRow>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Prop</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Type</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[120px]">Default</TableHead>
                    <TableHead>Description</TableHead>
                </TableRow>
            </TableHeader>
            <TableBody>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">From</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">object</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">0</TableCell><TableCell>Lower bound on the perpendicular axis. Required.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">To</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">object</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">0</TableCell><TableCell>Upper bound on the perpendicular axis. Required.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Axis</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ChartThresholdAxis</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Horizontal</TableCell><TableCell>Which axis the band is perpendicular to. Default Horizontal draws a yAxis band spanning the chart width.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Label</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Label rendered inside the band. Null or empty hides it.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Color</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">"#3b82f622"</TableCell><TableCell>Fill colour (typically a low-alpha hex like "#22c55e22"). Required — without it the zone would be invisible.</TableCell></TableRow>
            </TableBody>
        </Table>
    </div>

    <Heading Id="charttooltip" Level="3" Class="mt-8 scroll-mt-20">ChartTooltip</Heading>
    <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Class="mt-2">
        Declarative tooltip body for any chart wrapper. The child fragment is given a
        <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">ChartTooltipContext</code> on every hover and is rendered
        into a hidden DOM portal that ECharts' tooltip formatter pulls its <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">innerHTML</code>
        from — use this when you need real Razor markup (themed cards, formatted numbers, child components) instead
        of ECharts' raw formatter string.
    </Lumeo.Text>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
        <Table>
            <TableHeader>
                <TableRow>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Prop</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Type</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[120px]">Default</TableHead>
                    <TableHead>Description</TableHead>
                </TableRow>
            </TableHeader>
            <TableBody>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ChildContent</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">RenderFragment&lt;ChartTooltipContext&gt;</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">—</TableCell><TableCell>The tooltip body. Receives the current ChartTooltipContext for the hovered point. Required.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Class</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Extra classes for the rendered tooltip wrapper inside the portal.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">AdditionalAttributes</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Dictionary&lt;string, object&gt;?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Unmatched attributes flow through to the portal div so consumers can attach id, data-*, or ARIA attributes to the rendered tooltip wrapper.</TableCell></TableRow>
            </TableBody>
        </Table>
    </div>

    <Heading Id="chartskeleton" Level="3" Class="mt-8 scroll-mt-20">ChartSkeleton</Heading>
    <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Class="mt-2">
        The legacy SVG overlay skeleton used by <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">SkeletonStyle="ChartSkeletonStyle.Silhouette"</code>.
        Can also be rendered standalone as a static loading placeholder.
    </Lumeo.Text>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
        <Table>
            <TableHeader>
                <TableRow>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Prop</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Type</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[120px]">Default</TableHead>
                    <TableHead>Description</TableHead>
                </TableRow>
            </TableHeader>
            <TableBody>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Kind</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">ChartSkeletonKind</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Generic</TableCell><TableCell>Shape family drawn by the skeleton (Bars, Line, Area, Pie, Scatter, Grid, …).</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Width</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">"100%"</TableCell><TableCell>CSS width of the skeleton.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Height</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">"350px"</TableCell><TableCell>CSS height of the skeleton.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Class</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">string?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Additional CSS classes.</TableCell></TableRow>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">AdditionalAttributes</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Dictionary&lt;string, object&gt;?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Additional HTML attributes.</TableCell></TableRow>
            </TableBody>
        </Table>
    </div>

    <Heading Id="typed-chart-common-props" Level="3" Class="mt-8 scroll-mt-20">Typed chart wrapper common props</Heading>
    <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Class="mt-2">
        Every typed chart (<code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">BarChart</code>,
        <code class="text-xs bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 rounded">LineChart</code>, and the rest of the 30 chart types)
        exposes this parameter alongside its own data-shaping props:
    </Lumeo.Text>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
        <Table>
            <TableHeader>
                <TableRow>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Prop</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[180px]">Type</TableHead>
                    <TableHead Class="w-[120px]">Default</TableHead>
                    <TableHead>Description</TableHead>
                </TableRow>
            </TableHeader>
            <TableBody>
                <TableRow><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">OptionOverride</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">Dictionary&lt;string, object&gt;?</TableCell><TableCell Class="font-mono text-xs">null</TableCell><TableCell>Escape hatch: entries are merged into the generated EChartOption's extension data, letting you set any raw ECharts option key the typed wrapper doesn't expose a dedicated parameter for.</TableCell></TableRow>
            </TableBody>
        </Table>
    </div>
</div>

